find filter show before and after value {returnDocument},{projection to check selected valuw}
db.students.findOneAndUpdate(
            {name:"ullu"},---->filter
            {$set:{age:34}},---->prop
            {
                returnDocument:"after",
                projection:{name:1,age:1,_id:0}
            }
);

if the filter is not found it will give null
but want to add searched value
db.students.findOneAndUpdate(
            {name:"kohli"},
            {$set:{age:34,course:"bsc"}},
            {
                returnDocument:"after",
                projection:{name:1,age:1,_id:0},
                upsert:true
             }
         );//using upsert prop

sort prop(1 for accending order) and (-1 for decending order)
using sort we can update the result
db.students.findOneAndUpdate(
            {name:"kohli"},
            {$set:{age:34,course:"bsc"}},
            {
               sort:{age:1}
             }
         );
for finding and deleting 
db.students.findOneAndDelete(
            {name:"panna"},
            {projection:{name:1,age:1}}
         );
